{"cursor":"23640","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"{{Infobox NASCAR race\n| Name=Bojangles' Southern 500 Logo=Bojangles' Southern 500 logo.jpg\n| Img_size=frameless Venue=Darlington Raceway Sponsor=Bojangles' First race=1957\n| (NASCAR Convertible)  1963 (Sprint Cup) Distance=501.322 miles (806.799\n| km) Laps=367 Previous names='Rebel 300' (1957-1965) 'Rebel 400' (1966-\n| 1972) 'Rebel 500' (1973, 1975-1978) 'Rebel 450' (1974) 'CRC Chemicals\n| Rebel 500' (1979-1982) 'TranSouth 500' (1983-1993) 'TranSouth Financial\n| 400' (1994-1999) 'Mall.com 400' (2000) 'Carolina Dodge Dealers 400' (2001-\n| 2004) 'Dodge Charger 500' (2005-2006) 'Dodge Avenger 500'\n| (2007) 'Dodge Challenger 500' (2008) 'Southern 500 presented by\n| GoDaddy.com' (2009) 'Showtime Southern 500' (2010-2011)|\n}}\n\n:This article is about the race known as the Rebel 500 held on [[Confederate\nMemorial Day]] since 1957. For more information about the Grand Slam race which\nhad the same name from 1950 through 2004 and removed as part of the [[Ferko\nlawsuit]], see [[Southern 500 (1950-2004)|Mountain Dew Southern 500]].\n\nThe 'Bojangles' Southern 500' is the annual spring NASCAR Sprint Cup race held\nat Darlington Raceway in Darlington, South Carolina, USA, and is the second such\nevent at Darlington to bear the name. It began in 1957 as a race in the\nConvertible Division, known as the 'Rebel 300'. In 1966, the race was expanded\nto , and in 1973 to . In 1994, the race was returned to 400 miles. In 2005, as\npart of the settlement of the Ferko lawsuit and as part of a schedule\nrealignment, the \"Rebel\" returned to its classic Confederate Memorial Day\nweekend date, and raised back to 500 miles.\n\nWithout a title sponsor for 2009, the race tentatively adopted the moniker of\n'Southern 500', the traditional name of the fall race run from 1950-2004 on\nLabor Day weekend. A one-year deal with Go Daddy was signed. Some fans referred\nto the race exclusively as the GoDaddy.com 500 out of respect to what fans\ncalled the \"real\" Southern 500, a fall-race showdown. In 2010, Showtime signed a\nmulti-year deal to sponsor the race, giving it the name 'Showtime Southern 500'.\nIn 2012, Bojangles', a Charlotte-based quick-service reaturant, took over\nsponsorship of the \"Rebel\".\n","linknr":569,"url":"Southern_500","recorded":1362582741,"links":26,"instances":["automobile","nascar_driver","racing_driver"],"pdf":[],"categories":["1957 establishments in South Carolina","NASCAR races at Darlington Raceway|","NASCAR Sprint Cup Series races","Recurring sporting events established in 1957"],"headings":["Memorable moments","Past winners","Television broadcasters","External links"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/c/c6/Bojangles%27_Southern_500_logo.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[["southern_500","1950-2004"],["johnny_allen","racing_driver"],["david_pearson","nascar_driver"],["david_pearson","nascar_driver"],["mercury","automobile"],["david_pearson","nascar_driver"],["david_pearson","nascar_driver"],["mercury","automobile"],["david_pearson","nascar_driver"],["mercury","automobile"],["david_pearson","nascar_driver"],["mercury","automobile"],["david_pearson","nascar_driver"],["mercury","automobile"],["david_pearson","nascar_driver"]],"members":["mercury","david_pearson","johnny_allen","southern_500"],"related":["Darlington_Raceway","Bojangles'_Famous_Chicken_'n_Biscuits","NASCAR","Sprint_Cup","Darlington_Raceway","Darlington,_South_Carolina","USA","NASCAR_Convertible_Division","Confederate_Memorial_Day","Southern_500_(1950-2004)","Go_Daddy","Showtime_Networks","Bojangles'","Johnny_Allen_(racing_driver)","American_Broadcasting_Company","Darrell_Waltrip","Richard_Petty","Donnie_Allison","David_Pearson_(NASCAR_driver)","Wood_Brothers_Racing","Virgin